cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of predicting the intentions and actions of pedestrians in urban traffic environments using image sequences from a monocular RGB camera. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a real-time framework for this task, which involves tracking-by-detection and a novel spatio-temporal DenseNet model. This suggests that the paper could also fit into the categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training and evaluating the framework on real data, which could place it in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
